An SUV driver was arrested Thursday afternoon after he allegedly struck and killed a woman crossing a Bronx street, police said. The unidentified pedestrian was walking across Burke Avenue at Bouck Ave in the Laconia section around 12:30 p.m. when she was hit by the white Mercedes, according to cops. The driver of the vehicle, identified by police as Zavee Georges, 32, was taken into custody at the scene. Georges, of the Bronx, was charged with failure to yield to a pedestrian and failure to exercise due care, according to the NYPD.